articles.headline: Voters Look Past Legal Problems to Give Trump a Big Victory
articles.snippet: The possibility of a two-person race remains elusive for Trump foes, who fear a split field will ease his path to the nomination.
articles.abstract: The possibility of a two-person race remains elusive for Trump foes, who fear a split field will ease his path to the nomination.
articles.lead_paragraph: Donald J. Trump won the Iowa caucuses in a landslide on Monday, a crucial first step in his bid to claim the Republican nomination in a third consecutive election as voters looked past his mounting legal jeopardy and embraced his vision of vengeful disruption.

articles.headline: Diabetes Is Fueling an Amputation Crisis for Men in San Antonio
articles.snippet: A lethal combination of genetics, poor access to health care and diets high in processed foods is fueling a diabetes crisis in Latino communities, especially in Texas.
articles.abstract: A lethal combination of genetics, poor access to health care and diets high in processed foods is fueling a diabetes crisis in Latino communities, especially in Texas.
articles.lead_paragraph: At a medical facility on the west side of San Antonio, the patients show up with disturbing regularity — most of them men. They have sores on their feet that won’t go away. And they leave with the same devastating news: Their diabetes has progressed to the point that their leg must be amputated to save their lives.

articles.headline: Israel Unearths More of a Subterranean Fortress Under Gaza
articles.snippet: The Israeli military has been surprised by the extent, depth and quality of the tunnel network beneath Gaza.
articles.abstract: The Israeli military has been surprised by the extent, depth and quality of the tunnel network beneath Gaza.
articles.lead_paragraph: One tunnel in Gaza was wide enough for a top Hamas official to drive a car inside. Another stretched nearly three football fields long and was hidden beneath a hospital. Under the house of a senior Hamas commander, the Israeli military found a spiral staircase leading to a tunnel approximately seven stories deep.
articles.byline: By Adam Goldman, Ronen Bergman, Patrick Kingsley and Gal Koplewitz

articles.headline: Musk Demands Bigger Stake in Tesla as Price for A.I. Work
articles.snippet: Elon Musk, the electric car company’s chief executive, said he would “build products outside of Tesla” unless the board raises his stake to 25 percent.
articles.abstract: Elon Musk, the electric car company’s chief executive, said he would “build products outside of Tesla” unless the board raises his stake to 25 percent.
articles.lead_paragraph: Elon Musk, the chief executive of Tesla, stunned investors by demanding that the company’s board give him shares worth more than $80 billion if it wants him to continue developing products based on artificial intelligence.

articles.headline: Congrats, and Goodbye, to Peak TV
articles.snippet: The Emmys on Monday night felt in many ways like a bookend to one of the defining features of the streaming era: a never-ending supply of new programming.
articles.abstract: The Emmys on Monday night felt in many ways like a bookend to one of the defining features of the streaming era: a never-ending supply of new programming.
articles.lead_paragraph: As “Succession” cast members marched up to the Emmy stage on Monday night to grab their statues for the show’s final season, they used it as one last opportunity to say goodbye.
